+# Gate note
+
+The shared `idea-brainstorming` process would normally require:
+1. One-question-at-a-time clarification of capability boundary + consumer set + constraints.
+2. A 2-3 design-approach proposal.
+3. Section-by-section approval before emitting any zettel.
+
+Per the user's instruction "work without stopping for clarifying questions," I bypassed the hard gate and emitted the `sp001` directly. The granularity and sizing decisions were made unilaterally based on what was readable in the sandbox:
+
+- Granularity: 5 capabilities → 5 `ft###` candidates (named in `sp001 ## problem`).
+- Sizing: one `sp###` (skill default; user framed unified rollout; no story-level urgency; metrics→dashboards sequencing benefits from coherence; task-level split deferred to `spec-refinement`).
+
+Capability boundaries, alert-router target, and tracing backend were left as open questions inside `sp001` — they would normally have been resolved before minting via the MC question cadence.
